'''Otabek Shukurov''' (born 22 June 1996) is an Uzbek professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Baniyas Club|Baniyas]] and the [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]].<ref name="sw">{{cite web|title=O.Shukurov|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/otabek-shukurov/297337/|website=Soccerway|access-date=11 October 2016}}</ref>

==Club career==
Shukurov joined [[FK Mash'al Mubarek|Mash'al Mubarek]] in 2014 and made his league debut against [[PFK Metallurg Bekabad]] on 21 June 2014. On 1 January 2015, he moved to [[FC Bunyodkor]] where he played two league games before transferring to [[FK Buxoro]] on 15 July 2015. He had successful season in [[FK Buxoro]] by playing 14 games and scoring 2 goals and returned to FC Bunyodkor on 1 January 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/otabek-shukurov_prs372660/person.shtml|title = Otabek Shukurov - Player Profile - Football}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=April 2025}}

On 6 February 2024, it was announced that they had reached an agreement with the Turkish team [[Kayserispor]] and the agreement was signed on 9 February 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tribuna.uz/news/20/20/20/otabek-shukurov-kaiserispor-futbolchisiga-ailandi |title=Шукуров "Кайсериспор" футболчисига айланди |access-date=13 February 2024 |archive-date=8 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240208175459/https://tribuna.uz/news/20/20/20/otabek-shukurov-kaiserispor-futbolchisiga-ailandi |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>[https://championat.asia/oz/news/otabek-shukurov-turkiya-superligasi-vakili-bilan-deyarli-kelishib-boldi Otabek Shukurov Turkiya Superligasi vakili bilan deyarli kelishib bo'ldi]</ref>

The 28-year-old player moved from Kayserispor of Turkey to [[Al-Fayha FC|Al Fayha]] of Saudi Arabia in September 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.alfayhasc.com/blog/685|title=الأوزبكي أوتابيك شوكوروف فيحاوي لمدة موسم واحد|publisher=[[Al-Fayha FC]]|language=ar|date=3 September 2024|access-date=3 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribuna.uz/news/2024/09/03/otabek-shukurov--al-faia-futbolchisi|title=Otabek Shukurov Al Fayha futbolchisi|publisher=Tribuna.uz|language=uz|date=3 September 2024|access-date=3 September 2024}}</ref>

On 3 October 2025, Shukurov joined [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Baniyas Club|Baniyas]].<ref>{{cite web |title=بني ياس يتعاقد مع كروما وشوكوروف|url=https://www.emaratalyoum.com/sports/local/2025-10-03-1.1977084}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:TUR-UZB 20190113 Asian Cup 9.jpg|thumb|Otabek Shukurov (№19) at 2019 Asian Cup]]
Shukurov has represented his country at various age groups. He made his [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan national team]] debut against [[Lebanon national football team|Lebanon]] on 14 February 2016. In that match, Uzbekistan won by a score of 2–0.

Shukurov scored his first international goal on 11 October 2016 in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC third round|World Cup qualifying match]] against [[China national football team|China]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=12 October 2016 |title=Football: China, South Korea suffer World Cup blows |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/football-china-south-korea-suffer-world-cup-blows |access-date=11 April 2025 |work=The Straits Times |language=en |issn=0585-3923}}</ref>

Ranked in Uzbekistan squad for [[FIFA World Cup 2026]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://t.me/uzpfl/77948|title=UzPFL|website=Telegram|access-date=2026-05-29}}</ref>

